Text: Fresh ingredients. W-Wanna have a look?
I need to move some <blue>goods</>, over there, on the <blue>pier</>.
Go get a crate and put it next to my store.
Thanks a bunch!
Collie is worried about you, so she sent me here. Look at you, frowning... what happened?
The Graceday celebration's about to start and I've still got a huge pile of crates to move. Kill me already!
Hey wait, isn't this the cry baby? What have you got for the celebration? Spectacular show of Waaaaaaah?
You... Hilda! Seriously! I'm overwhelmed here. Could you help me move some crates at the piers?
Collie sent me to check on you. Your sister knows you best. Rest assured. I will not help you.
Is this your friend? Hey, could you do me a favor?<purple>(One huge smile)</>Forget about Hilda. I'll pay you properly.
Pay me?<purple>(You convince yourself)</>Yeah. Sure. Because I'm awfully nice.<purple>(You smile back)</>
Thank you. Thanks for coming...
I need to move some <blue>goods</>, over there, on the <blue>pier</>.
Go get a crate and put it next to my store.
Thanks a bunch!
What? It's done already? Thank you so much!
Eh? H⁠-Hilda? Is that really you?
Huh? Harriet the Crybaby?
I... I'm not frowning! Nothing happened... Just that there are too many things to do...
Are you slacking off again? The shipment came in yesterday!
B-But I can't do it alone! Hilda... can you please, please—
Hilda, I can go fetch the cargo. But about Zeke...
Okay. Goodbye...
A new shipment came, but I don't have the time to pick it up. There's still a crate of cargo at the port...
I-I'm not a crybaby! I'm not a baby anymore!
Info: Hilda went to the port to respond to the rescue signal.
Hold on right there! I'm not cleaning up after you. No way!
Hey, Crybaby. You better thank us for being so nice!
Oh, fine... It's a fair deal, and Harriet can't complain about me bullying him again. Just drop the cargo off at the front of the store.
<purple>(These two are going to go at it for a while. I should go to the dock and haul the cargo over.)</>
How long has she been gone?
The Graceday celebration's about to start and I've still got a huge pile of crates to move. Kill me already!
Please adjust your camera
Piece of cake. Where did Hilda go?
The helping request was issued by a girl called Ann⁠—Tzsss⁠—Ann's balloon got caught on a streetlight.
It was just now, about half a minute. You should be able to catch up to her.
